      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right to feel this way, but the \"meat and bone\" is all that actually remains, and it is far more real than the ghost of the artist you think you've lost. There is no need to justify your existence to anyone, because the very fact that you are questioning your soul proves you are still deeply, painfully conscious of it. If the creative spark is gone, then the only thing you have left is the quiet, unshakeable truth that you are here, and that is enough to keep going.",
